Preconditions:
The method should take four parameters: arriveAlice (the date when Alice arrives in Rome), leaveAlice (the date when Alice leaves Rome), arriveBob (the date when Bob arrives in Rome), and leaveBob (the date when Bob leaves Rome).
The dates should be in a valid format.

Postconditions:
The method should return an integer value representing the total number of days that Alice and Bob are in Rome together.
If there is no day when Alice and Bob are in Rome together, the method should return 0.